Doxee Salesforce Query Builder allows you to create Salesforce SOQL queries using a graphical wizard.

The individual steps are described in detail below, but first, an overview of the sequence is described.

Overview: Using the Doxee Salesforce Query it is possible to select the respective object from all objects available in your Salesforce instance (including custom objects). After selecting the object all available attributes of this object will be displayed and offered for selection. To limit the results of the query it is possible to set filters on attribute level as well as to define a sort order in case of multiple results. The Doxee Salesforce Querybuilder allows to store of these so-called query objects which are stored in their own Doxee custom objects within Salesforce.

## Opening the Doxee Salesforce Query Builder 
To start the Doxee Salesforce Query Builder you first have to select the app "Doxee Setup" in the Salesforce App Launcher. 

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

Salesforce App Launcher - "Doxee Setup" app is here on the bottom right. 

After selecting the "*Doxee Setup*" app, the pages with the subsections will open:

- Doxee Queries

- Doxee Query Builder

- Doxee Business Designer

Here you select the *Doxee Query Builder *section and enter the wizard whose steps are described in the following chapters.

## Selection of the desired object 
In the first step of the wizard, the desired object is selected. All objects available in your Salesforce instance are displayed. Both the display name and the technical name. Choose the object and continue to the next steps. In the second step, you select fields that you would like to use in your query. In the third step, you can add filtering or sorting criteria to your query. In the last step, you save your query, and you can download an XML file with sample data. The XML file can be then used during design phase in Business Designer or Process Designer.
